      <!-- ================================================================ -->
      <!-- TEXT 2 — English translation                                     -->
      <!--                                                                  -->
      <!-- Each <seg corresp="#seg-N"> corresponds to <seg xml:id="seg-N"> -->
      <!-- in the Latin edition above. In TEI Publisher this can be         -->
      <!-- configured to render as a parallel column.                       -->
      <!-- ================================================================ -->
      <text xml:lang="en" type="translation">
        <body>
          <p>
            <seg corresp="#seg1">Following the effects of the Body of
              Christ,</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg2"> just as Reymundus says: this sacrament of the Body of
              Christ accomplishes eternity and immortality for those who take it
              worthily, and the opposite for those who do not.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg3"> The Apostle [says]: let a man examine himself,
              and thus is understood what is said — carefully consider what is
              served to you, certainly such as the host of Christ. Hence</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg4"> the verse: White, wheaten, thin, not large,
              round, without yeast, not false — the host of Christ should
              be.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg5"> Gloss: White signifies chastity.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg6"> Thus you should be white, that is chaste in
              body and heart.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg7"> Wheaten: wheat is the sweetest of all grain,
              so you should be sweet and gentle.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg8"> Thin: that is moderate in food and
              drink.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg9"> Not large: that is humble, not proud.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg10"> Round: such as a round shape is moveable, so
              you should be moveable for the divine office and for doing certain
              good deeds.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg11"> Without yeast: yeast signifies envy and
              anger, that is you should have a sincere heart, fully devoted to
              God and your neighbour.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg12"> Not false: that is without greed and
              avarice.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg13"> Hence Jerome [says]: I do not remember having
              read of anyone being damned who in this world led a decent life,
              that is [one of] great generosity in deed, and so on.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg14"> Following, as Ecclesiasticus says: he who
              worthily takes this sacrament receives thirteen blessings.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg15"> Hence the verse: I increase, I mingle, I
              soothe, I restrain, I terrify, I cleanse. I ignite, I enlighten,
              I double. I strengthen, I draw near, I lead. And I give life;
              upon the table so many dishes I place.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg16"> Gloss — I increase: namely grace in the
              present and glory in the future.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg17"> I mingle: that is I make [one]
              gentler.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg18"> I soothe: namely temptations.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg19"> I restrain: that is evil affection and the
              desire of the flesh.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg20"> I terrify: namely demons, for the demons fear
              nothing so much as the Body of Christ.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg21"> Hence Chrysostomus [says]: the Body of Christ
              repels demons and calls angels, and rightly so, because where
              their Lord is, his angels are too.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg22"> I cleanse: namely venial sins.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg23"> I ignite: namely your affection and spirit
              toward good.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg24"> I enlighten: namely your
              understanding.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg25"> I double: that is I multiply merit here and
              merit there.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg26"> I strengthen: namely the virtues within
              you.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg27"> I draw near: that is I shall be familiar in
              your soul.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg28"> I lead: namely out of misery and mourning to
              joy.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg29"> I give: namely eternal life.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg30"> A M E N</seg>
          </p>
        </body>
      </text>

